Dundee Stars sun rama rashin nasarar da suka sha a ranar Juma'a a hannun Belfast Giants a gasar Elite League, inda suka ci wasan da aka yi a gida da ci 5-3 a ranar Asabar.
A sakamakon bugun da Patrick Dwyer da Francis Baville suka yi, Giants sun ci gaba da kaiwa da kwallo biyu a farkon wasan.
Mike Sullivan da Jordan Cooney sun daidaita kafin Dwyer ya sake zama shugaban Giants.
François Bouchard daga Dundee ya daidaita ci, bayan haka Lucas Lundwald Nielsen ya ba da kwallo biyu don tabbatar da nasarar.
Wannan ne karo na uku da aka doke 'yan wasan Adam Keefe a gasar Premier a kakar wasa ta bana, inda suka doke Dundee 2-1 a Belfast a ranar Juma'a da yamma.
Kungiyoyin sun hadu a karo na hudu a kakar wasa; Giants sun ci wasanni uku da suka gabata.
Duayer ya zira kwallo ta farko a minti na hudu (03:35) daga wasan Kendall McFall, kuma bayan minti hudu Bavilio ya ninka lambar bayan wasan David Rutherford.
A lokacin farko mai cike da tashin hankali (13:10) Sullivan ya bude ci daga hannun masu gida, sannan Coon ya daidaita ci bayan wucewar Matt Markward (15:16).
Dwyer ya tabbatar wa Giants da jagorancin lokacin da suka shiga hutu na farko, inda ya zira kwallo ta biyu a wasan a ƙarshen lokaci na farko.
Mai karɓar ya sake haɗuwa, kuma Bouchard ya sake daidaita lissafin, ya zira kwallo a gaban tawagar (27:37).
Kaun da Charles Corcoran sun taimaka wa Nielsen ya jagoranci Dundee a karon farko a wasan a ƙarshen lokaci na biyu, kuma ya tabbatar da nasara tare da lambar biyar ta ƙungiyar a tsakiyar lokacin ƙarshe.
Giants, da suka yi rashin nasara a wasanni hudu daga cikin biyar da suka gabata, za su buga wasan karshe a gida da Milton Keynes ranar Juma'a.
